    "# Classification on EmuCore\n",
    "#### Device: EmuCore\n",
    "\n",
    "## Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "We contribute to the ongoing advancements in the field of reservoir computing by presenting an innovative demonstration of a fully-integrated opto-electronic RC system. Our setup incorporates a Mach-Zehnder electro-optic modulator (EOM) along with a FPGA circuit, marking a significant step towards compactness and stability compared to traditional fiber-optic approaches. By digitally implementing both the delay line and filters within the FPGA, we achieve robust immunity to optical drifts and noise. This design not only enhances the system's reliability but also enables greater dynamic range and connectivity among reservoir nodes, facilitated by leveraging FPGA-based filters. Our work underscores the potential of integrating digital signal processing capabilities into optical computing paradigms, paving the way for more efficient and versatile reservoir computing applications.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Reservoir Computing\n",
    "\n",
    "Reservoir computing (RC) initially utilized analog electronics with a single nonlinear node and delayed feedback for information processing. As technology progressed, digital electronics, notably field programmable gate arrays (FPGAs), gained prominence due to their compactness, stability, affordability, and adaptability with various commercial systems for real-time tasks. Recently, there has been a notable advance in hybrid opto-electronic systems incorporating FPGAs, particularly in developing coherent Ising machines for solving complex optimization problems. These systems also facilitate the construction of extensive networks of interconnected nodes, enabling the study of phenomena like cluster synchronization, chimera states, and laminar chaos. These innovations highlight the integration of digital and optical technologies, enhancing our ability to tackle intricate computational challenges and explore dynamic behaviors in networked systems.\n",
    "\n",
    "<img src=\"figures/general_reservoir_schematic.png\" alt=\"fishy\" class=\"bg-primary mb-1\" width=\"400px\">\n",
    "\n",
    "### Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN)\n",
    "\n",
    "Here we use a Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN) architecture as our reservoir.\n",
    "\n",
    "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Recurrent_neural_network\n",
    "\n",
    "<img src=\"figures/rnn_model.png\" alt=\"fishy\" class=\"bg-primary mb-1\" width=\"500px\" >\n",
    "\n",
    "<img src=\"figures/rnn_reservoir_schematic.png\" alt=\"fishy\" class=\"bg-primary mb-1\" width=\"500px\">\n",
    "\n",
    "### QCi's EmuCore\n",
    "\n",
    "QCI's EmuCore technology is based a time delayed scheme.\n",
    "\n",
    "<img src=\"figures/time_delayed_reservoir_schematic.png\" alt=\"fishy\" class=\"bg-primary mb-1\" width=\"500px\">\n",
    "\n",
    "https://arxiv.org/pdf/2102.09049.pdf\n"
   ]
  },
